  "notes": "Romansh (Rumantsch). Rhaeto-Romance language of Graubünden, Switzerland. ~60,000 speakers. National language since 1938. Written standard: Rumantsch Grischun (1982). Five spoken idioms: Sursilvan, Sutsilvan, Surmiran, Puter, Vallader. Key features: (1) CA- palatalisation. (2) Front rounded vowels /y/. (3) Heavy German contact influence (Liver 1999).",
